Description: Sherd of floor and ring foot of pottery open vessel (bowl?); micaceous dull brown clay. Remains of light brown paint on some surfaces. Incised inscription on floor.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 642)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (IC.051)
